# Microsoft-Inspired UI Rules

- Follow `docs/13-MICROSOFT-INSPIRED-UX-STANDARDS.md` for all UI changes.
- Keep enterprise visual tone: neutral surfaces, one primary brand accent, clear hierarchy.
- Use consistent states for controls: rest, hover (web), pressed, focus-visible, disabled.
- Enforce accessibility defaults: visible focus ring, WCAG-AA contrast, labels for icon-only controls.
- Keep role-based UX explicit for `ADMIN`, `MANAGER`, `EMPLOYEE` without changing domain naming.
- Prefer concise, action-oriented labels: "Assign Task", "Update Progress", "Approve Leave".
- Ensure loading/empty/error/success states exist for changed screens and flows.
